cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Generative Layers in your research or software, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
title: "Generative Layers"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Kyriakidis"
    given-names: "Dimitrios"
abstract: >
  Generative Layers is a Java framework for governed generative resource layers
  in BDI-first and agent-oriented systems. It supports controlled access to
  external generative resources such as LLMs, tools, APIs, and services while
  preserving a boundary between generated candidate material and the host
  agent platform's internal beliefs, intentions, plans, and actions.
keywords:
  - "BDI agents"
  - "multi-agent systems"
  - "agent-oriented programming"
  - "generative AI"
  - "LLM governance"
  - "ASTRA"
  - "Jason"
  - "JaCaMo"
license: "Apache-2.0"
url: "https://www.generativelayers.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/generativelayers/framework"
